  "description": "But never accepting it",
  "body_html": "<p>I get confused a lot.</p><p>I\u2019ve spent</p><ul><li><p>years trying to get to research level physics skill</p></li><li><p>years trying to do a quantum chemistry project </p></li><li><p>months figuring out how to best use <a href=\"https://casualphysicsenjoyer.com/Essays+in+progress/Biosecurity/Far+UVC/Zonal+Models+for+CFD\">physics in a biosecurity context</a></p></li><li><p>months figuring out how to set up an <a href=\"https://www.independentscience.org/\">independent science community </a></p></li><li><p>weeks trying to learn LEAN syntax for <a href=\"https://physlean.com/\">PhysLEAN</a>. </p></li><li><p>several hours trying to do a <a href=\"https://casualphysicsenjoyer.com/Essays+in+progress/Theoretical+Physics/Condensed+Matter+Theory/The+Periodic+Hopping+Model+And+Spontaneous+Symmetry+Breaking\">tricky integral from Shankar\u2019s condensed matter theory</a></p></li></ul><p>For all of these things, I seem to live in a constant state of confusion. I am usually too confused to understand what the problems are. And if I do, I still get confused on terminology, novel content, mechanisms, relative importance, and math. </p><p>Having more experience doesn\u2019t get rid of confusion. Rather, my feeling of confusion has stayed at a constant whirr. Nature has infinite levels of detail, and the deeper you go, the more confusing the levels appear. </p><p>So, to move forward, I have to do things despite being confused. It\u2019s like being on an endless, wobbly treadmill. I have to make decisions, write code, do math, and email people with imperfect knowledge of what I am talking about. </p><p>It often feels like rearranging symbols around in some pattern-matchy way without understanding what they mean yet. And this leads to making decisions filled with uncertainty. </p><p>But I don\u2019t think that one should <em>accept</em> confusion. Rather, the furthest I am willing to go is to <em>tolerate</em> confusion, like a guest overstaying in my house for eternity. </p><p>Or, like how my girlfriend tolerates my overly loud chewing. (Sorry Amelia). </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!f2Dr!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82b8a8d3-e902-4b85-affd-70cf0f0d2d73_514x634.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!f2Dr!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82b8a8d3-e902-4b85-affd-70cf0f0d2d73_514x634.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!f2Dr!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82b8a8d3-e902-4b85-affd-70cf0f0d2d73_514x634.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!f2Dr!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82b8a8d3-e902-4b85-affd-70cf0f0d2d73_514x634.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!f2Dr!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82b8a8d3-e902-4b85-affd-70cf0f0d2d73_514x634.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!f2Dr!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F82b8a8d3-e902-4b85-affd-70cf0f0d2d73_514x634.png\" width=\"514\" height=\"634\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/82b8a8d3-e902-4b85-affd-70cf0f0d2d73_514x634.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:634,&quot;width&